      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING HOPKINS (7) finished in the placings last time but could not have been more impressive before that in his blistering 29.62 win at this track over 520m. Hard to top on the time from two back. BOTH BOWERS ACE (5) had won two starts on end before the winning streak was broken with a second placing (29.86) last time at this track. Has a good record here including 16 wins. Super consistent and can feature with the right run. SAMMY ETHAN (4) skirted wide from an outside draw last start and found the front, leading throughout to win (29.63) at this track in a Mix 2/3 over 520m. Goes well out of this box with a win and six minor placings. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. ZIPPING GRYLLIS (8) was strongly fancied last time but finished fifth (21.02) at Nowra, bringing a two-run winning streak to an end.",
